  "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nAs [discussed on Zulip](https://quarkusio.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/187030-users/topic/2.2E11.3A.20trailing.20slash.20in.20rest-client/near/291546201), Quarkus 2.11 introduces a change in `quarkus-rest-client-reactive`: trailing slashes are removed from REST paths. This makes it impossible to call a remote server that requires a trailing slash.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nTrailing slashes should be preserved.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nTrailing slashes are removed. The calls fail with a 404 status when the remote server does not accept requests without a trailing slash.\r\n\r\n### How to Reproduce?\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Quarkus version or git rev\r\n\r\n2.11.0.Final",
